            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Imperatores <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Caes</abbr><ex>ares</ex></expan> Aurelius Antoninus</supplied> <lb n="2"/>et Aurelius Com<supplied reason="lost">modus Augusti praetorium<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> ve</supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/>tustate conlabsu<supplied reason="lost">m! a solo restituerunt per</supplied> <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionem</ex></expan> I <expan><abbr>Ital</abbr><ex>icam</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ublio</ex></expan> Cal&amp;lt;p=B&amp;gt;urni<supplied reason="lost">o Iuliano <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ato</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Augg</abbr><ex>ustorum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pr</abbr><ex>o</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pr</abbr><ex>aetore</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>prov</abbr><ex>inciae</ex></expan> Moesiae <expan><abbr>inf</abbr><ex>erioris</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="5"/>et <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aio</ex></expan> Sammucio Maiore <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">leg(ato) leg(ionis) I Ital(icae)? ---</supplied> 
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Dipinto-Inschrift. Text mit roter Farbe auf den Stein aufgetragen. Z. 5: maßgebliche Neulesung durch Bunsch - Mrozewicz. C(aio) Sammucio Maiore (zuvor: cura(nte) Mucio Maiore).</p>
            </div>
